Class AbsParcelableLceViewState<D,V extends MvpLceView<D>>

  • Type Parameters:
    D - the data / model type
    V - the type of the view
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    LceViewState<D,V>, ParcelableLceViewState<D,V>, RestoreableParcelableViewState<V>, RestoreableViewState<V>, ViewState<V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArrayListLceViewState, CastedArrayListLceViewState, ParcelableDataLceViewState, SerializeableLceViewState, VoidViewState

    public abstract class AbsParcelableLceViewState<D,V extends MvpLceView<D>>
extends AbsLceViewState<D,V>
implements ParcelableLceViewState<D,V>
    Extends AbsLceViewState by implementing RestoreableViewState. This class can be saved and restored in a bundle. Therefore it can be used for Activities and Fragments.

    Please note, that restoreInstanceState(Bundle)

    will create a new copy of this view state and return that one instead of the current object instance. That's fine and makes working custom view states much easier. This note is just to inform you that the view state refrence attached to the view may change during restroing view state.
    Since:
    1.0.0
